#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:281
msgid ""
"You can be use `.mac` files for writing own library of macros. But since "
"they don’t contain enough structural information they cannot be read back as "
"a _wxMaxima_ session."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:283
msgid "### .wxm"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:285
msgid ""
".wxm files contains the worksheet except _maxima_'s output. On maxima "
"versions >5.38 they can be read using _Maxima_'s `load()` function just as ."
"mac files can be. With this plain-text format it sometimes is unavoidable "
"that worksheets that use new features are not downwards-compatible with "
"older versions of _wxMaxima_."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:287
msgid "### .wxmx"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:289
msgid ""
"This xml-based file format saves the complete worksheet including things "
"like the zoom factor and the watchlist. It is the preferred file format."
msgstr ""

