#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:354
msgid "## User feedback in the statusbar"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:356
msgid ""
"Long-running commands can provide user-feedback in the status bar. This user "
"feedback is replaced by any new feedback that is placed there (allowing to "
"use it as a progress indicator) and is deleted as soon as the current "
"command sent to _maxima_ is finished. It is safe to use `wxstatusbar()` even "
"in libraries that might be used with plain _Maxima_ (as opposed to "
"_wxMaxima_): If _wxMaxima_ isn't present the `wxstatusbar()` command will "
"just be left unevelated."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:363
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    (%i2)\tfor i:1 thru 10 do (\n"
"\t            /* Tell the user how far we got */\n"
"\t            wxstatusbar(concat(\"Pass \",i)),\n"
"\t            /* A truly long-running command */\n"
"\t           a:makelist(o^i,o,1,100000)\n"
"\t        )$\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:365
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:704
msgid "## Plotting"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:367
msgid ""
"Plotting (having fundamentally to do with graphics) is a place where a "
"graphical user interface will have to provide some extensions to the "
"original program."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:369
msgid "### Embedding a plot into the work sheet"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:371
msgid ""
"_Maxima_ normally instructs the external program gnuplot to open a separate "
"window for every diagram it creates. Since many times it is convenient to "
"embed graphs into the work sheet instead _wxMaxima_ provides its own set of "
"plot functions that don’t differ from the corresponding _maxima_ functions "
"save in their name: They are all prefixed by a “wx”. For example `wxplot` "
"corresponds to `plot`, `wxdraw` corresponds to `draw` and `wxhistogram` "
"corresponds to `histogram`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:373
msgid "### Making embedded plots bigger or smaller"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:375
msgid ""
"As noted above, the configure dialog provides a way to change the default "
"size plots are created with which sets the starting value of `wxplot_size`. "
"The plotting routines of _wxMaxima_ respect this variable that specifies the "
"size of a plot in pixels. It can always be queried or used to set the size "
"of the following plots:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:378
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    %i1 wxplot_size:[1200,800];\n"
"    %o1 [1200,800];\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:385
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    %i2 wxdraw2d(\n"
"        explicit(\n"
"            sin(x),\n"
"            x,1,10\n"
"        )\n"
"    )$\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:387
msgid ""
"If the size of only one plot is to be changed _Maxima_ provides a canonical "
"way to change an attribute only for the current cell."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:390
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"     %i1 wxplot_size:[1200,800];\n"
"     %o1 [1200,800];\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:397
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"     %i1 wxdraw2d(\n"
"             explicit(\n"
"                 sin(x),\n"
"                 x,1,10\n"
"             )\n"
"         ),wxplot_size=[1600,800]$\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:404
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    %i1 wxdraw2d(\n"
"        explicit(\n"
"            sin(x),\n"
"            x,1,10\n"
"        )\n"
"    ),wxplot_size=[1600,800]$\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:407
msgid "### Better quality plots"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:409
msgid ""
"Gnuplot doesn’t seem to provide a portable way of determining whether it "
"supports the high-quality bitmap output the cairo library provides. On "
"systems where gnuplot is compiled to use this library the pngcairo option "
"from the configuration menu (that can be overridden by the variable "
"`wxplot_pngcairo`) enables support for antialiasing and additional line "
"styles."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:411
msgid "### Opening up plots in interactive gnuplot windows"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:413
msgid ""
"If a plot was generated using the `wxdraw`-type commands (`wxplot` isn't "
"supported by this feature) and the file size of the underlying gnuplot "
"project isn't way too high _wxMaxima_ offers a right-click menu that allows "
"to open the plot in an interactive gnuplot window."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:415
msgid ""
"### Opening gnuplot's command console in windows created by `plot` and `draw`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:417
msgid ""
"On MS Windows if in _Maxima_'s variable `gnuplot_command` \"gnuplot\" is "
"replaced by \"wgnuplot\" gnuplot offers the possibility to open a console "
"window gnuplot commands can be entered into. Unfortunately enabling this "
"feature causes gnuplot to \"steal\" the keyboard focus for a short time "
"every time a plot is prepared."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:419
msgid "### Embedding animations into the spreadsheet"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:421
msgid ""
"The `with_slider_draw` command is a version of `wxdraw2d` that does prepare "
"multiple plots and allows to switch between them by moving the slider on top "
"of the screen. If ImageMagick is installed _wxMaxima_ even allows to export "
"this animation as an animated gif."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:423
msgid ""
"The first two arguments for `with_slider_draw` are the name of the variable "
"that is stepped between the plots and a list of the values of these "
"variable. The arguments that follow are the ordinary arguments for "
"`wxdraw2d`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:432
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    with_slider_draw(\n"
"        f,[1,2,3,4,5,6,7,10],\n"
"        title=concat(\"f=\",f,\"Hz\"),\n"
"        explicit(\n"
"            sin(2*%pi*f*x),\n"
"            x,0,1\n"
"        ),grid=true\n"
"    );\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:434
msgid ""
"The same functionality for 3D plots is accessible as `with_slider_draw3d`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:436
msgid "There is a second set of functions making use of the slider"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '*   '
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:439
msgid "`wxanimate_draw` and"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '*   '
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:439
msgid "`wxanimate_draw3d`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:444
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    wxanimate_draw(\n"
"        a, 3,\n"
"        explicit(sin(a*x), x, -4, 4),\n"
"        title=printf(false, \"a=~a\", a));\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:446
msgid ""
"Normally the animations are played back or exported with the frame rate "
"chosen in the configuration of _wxMaxima_. To set the speed an individual "
"animation is played back the variable wxanimate\\_framerate can be used:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:449
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    wxanimate(a, 10,\n"
"        sin(a*x), [x,-5,5]), wxanimate_framerate=6$\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:451
msgid ""
"The animation functions have a pitfall that one has to be aware of when "
"using them: The slider variable's value are substituted into the expression "
"that is to be plotted - which will fail, if the variable isn't directly "
"visible in the expression. Therefore the following example will fail:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:459
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    f:sin(a*x);\n"
"    with_slider_draw(\n"
"        a,makelist(i/2,i,1,10),\n"
"        title=concat(\"a=\",float(a)),\n"
"        grid=true,\n"
"        explicit(f,x,0,10)\n"
"    )$\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:461
msgid ""
"If _Maxima_ is forced to first evaluate the expression and then asked to "
"substitute the slider’s value plotting works fine instead:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:469
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    f:sin(a*x);\n"
"    with_slider_draw(\n"
"        a,makelist(i/2,i,1,10),\n"
"        title=concat(\"a=\",float(a)),\n"
"        grid=true,\n"
"        explicit(''f,x,0,10)\n"
"    )$\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:471
msgid "### Opening multiple plots in contemporaneous windows"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:473
msgid ""
"While not being a provided by _wxMaxima_ this feature of _Maxima_ (on setups "
"that support it) sometimes comes in handily. The following example comes "
"from a post from Mario Rodriguez to the _Maxima_ mailing list:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:475
#, no-wrap
msgid "    load(draw);\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:478
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    /* Parabola in window #1 */\n"
"    draw2d(terminal=[wxt,1],explicit(x^2,x,-1,1));\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:481
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    /* Parabola in window #2 */\n"
"    draw2d(terminal=[wxt,2],explicit(x^2,x,-1,1));\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:484
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    /* Paraboloid in window #3 */\n"
"    draw3d(terminal=[wxt,3],explicit(x^2+y^2,x,-1,1,y,-1,1));\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:486
msgid "### The \"Plot using draw\" sidepane"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:488
msgid ""
"The \"Plot using draw\" sidebar hides a simple code generator that allows to "
"generate scenes that make use of some of the flexibility of the _draw_ "
"package _maxima_ comes with."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:490
msgid "#### 2D"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:492
msgid ""
"Generates the sceleton of a `draw()` command that draws a 2D scene. This "
"scene later has to be filled with commands that generate the scene's "
"contents, for example by using the buttons in the rows below the \"2D\" "
"button."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:494
msgid ""
"One helpful feature of the 2D button is that it allows to setup the scene as "
"an animation in which a variable (by default it is _t_ has a different value "
"in each frame: Often an moving 2D plot allows easier interpretation than the "
"same data in a non-moving 3D one."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:496
msgid "#### 3D"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:498
msgid ""
"Generates the sceleton of a `draw()` command that draws a 3D scene. If "
"neither a 2D or a 3D scene are set up all of the other buttons set up a 2D "
"scene that contains the command the button generates."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:500
msgid "#### Expression"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:502
msgid ""
"Appends a standard plot of an expression like `sin(x)`, `x*sin(x)` or "
"`x^2+2*x-4` to the `draw()` command the cursor currently is in. If there is "
"no draw command a 2D scene with the plot is generated. Each scene can be "
"filled with any number of plots."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:504
msgid "#### Implicit plot"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:506
msgid ""
"Tries to find all points an expression like `y=sin(x)`, `y*sin(x)=3` or "
"`x^2+y^2=4` is true at and plots the resulting curve in the `draw()` command "
"the cursor currently is in. If there is no draw command a 2D scene with the "
"plot is generated."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:508
msgid "#### Parametric plot"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:510
msgid ""
"Steps a variable from a lower limit to an upper limit and uses two "
"expressions like `t*sin(t)` and `t*cos(t)` for generating the x, y (and in "
"3D plots also z) coordinates of a curve that is put into the current draw "
"command."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:512
msgid "#### Points"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:514
msgid ""
"Draws many points that can optionally be joined. The coordinates of the "
"points are taken from a list of lists, an 2D array or one list or array for "
"each axis."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:516
msgid "#### Diagram title"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:518
msgid "Draws a title on the upper end of the diagram,"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:520
msgid "#### Axis"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:522
msgid "Sets up the axis."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:524
msgid "#### Contour"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:526
msgid ""
"(Only for 3D plots): Adds contour lines similar to the ones one can find in "
"a map of a mountain to the plot commands that follow in the current draw() "
"command and/or to the ground plane of the diagram. Alternatively this wizard "
"allows skipping drawing the curves entirely only showing the contour plot."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:528
msgid "#### Plot name"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:530
msgid ""
"Adds a legend entry showing the next plot's name to the legend of the "
"diagram. An empty name disables generating legend entries for the following "
"plots."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:532
msgid "#### Line color"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:534
msgid ""
"Sets the line color for the following plots the current draw command "
"contains."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:536
msgid "#### Fill color"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:538
msgid ""
"Sets the fill color for the following plots the current draw command "
"contains."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:540
msgid "#### Grid"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:542
msgid "Pops up a wizard that allows to set up grid lines."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:544
msgid "#### Accuracy"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/gunter/src/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:546
